          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "5Wpkr",
          "name": "Article Body Section",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "gap": 48,
          "padding": [
            48,
            64
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "wC10q",
              "name": "Article Content",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 24,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "32Fyf",
                  "name": "lede",
                  "fill": "$--foreground",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "In a landmark moment for American governance, Senate leaders from both parties unveiled a sweeping $2.3 trillion infrastructure package on Tuesday that promises to reshape the nation's roads, bridges, broadband networks, and clean energy systems over the next decade.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 18,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "line",
                  "id": "ZtKTS",
                  "name": "divider1",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 0,
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$--border"
                  }
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "PECcz",
                  "name": "p1",
                  "fill": "$--foreground",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The proposal, which has been months in the making, represents a rare instance of bipartisan cooperation in an increasingly polarized political landscape. It allocates $645 billion for transportation infrastructure, $400 billion for broadband expansion, $300 billion for clean energy initiatives, and the remainder spread across water systems, housing, and education facilities.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "fTHnd",
                  "name": "h2",
                  "fill": "$--foreground",
                  "content": "A Historic Investment in Transportation",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.3
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "vcMKA",
                  "name": "p2",
                  "fill": "$--foreground",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The transportation portion of the bill addresses what experts have long described as a crisis in American infrastructure. According to the American Society of Civil Engineers, the country's infrastructure received a C-minus grade in its most recent report card, with an estimated $2.59 trillion in needed repairs over the next decade.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "FV6N5",
                  "name": "Quote Block",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$--muted",
                  "stroke": {
                    "align": "inside",
                    "thickness": {
                      "left": 4
                    },
                    "fill": "$--border"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": [
                    24,
                    32
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "oNVMj",
                      "name": "quoteText",
                      "fill": "$--foreground",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "\"This is not a Democratic plan or a Republican plan. This is an American plan, and it's long overdue. Our infrastructure has been crumbling for decades, and today we take the first step toward fixing it.\"",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "normal",
                      "fontStyle": "italic"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "OFz5W",
                      "name": "quoteAuthor",
                      "fill": "$--muted-foreground",
                      "content": "— Senator Maria Collins (D-WA), Co-sponsor",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 14,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "d4u9t",
                  "name": "h3",
                  "fill": "$--foreground",
                  "content": "Broadband for All Americans",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.3
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "ePWgp",
                  "name": "p3",
                  "fill": "$--foreground",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Perhaps the most transformative element of the package is its $400 billion investment in broadband infrastructure. The plan aims to bring high-speed internet access to every American household by 2030, with particular emphasis on rural and underserved communities that have long been left behind in the digital revolution.",
