              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "pk9uL",
          "name": "Article Body",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 24,
          "padding": [
            32,
            20
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "7ZCvz",
              "name": "lede",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "In a landmark moment for American governance, a bipartisan group of senators today unveiled the most ambitious infrastructure proposal in decades — a sweeping $2.3 trillion package that promises to reshape the nation's roads, bridges, broadband networks, and clean energy systems over the next eight years.",
              "lineHeight": 1.7,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "line",
              "id": "VK6Xy",
              "name": "divider",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 0,
              "stroke": {
                "thickness": 1,
                "fill": "$--border"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "2257T",
              "name": "body1",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The proposal, which has been months in the making, represents a rare moment of bipartisan cooperation in an increasingly polarized Washington. Led by Senators from both parties, the plan addresses what experts have long called a crisis-level deterioration of American infrastructure while also investing heavily in the technologies of the future.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "meit8",
              "name": "Lede",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "In a landmark moment for American governance, Senate leaders from both parties stood together Tuesday to announce what they called the most ambitious infrastructure package in the nation's history. The $2.3 trillion proposal aims to modernize everything from crumbling highways to rural broadband networks, marking a rare show of bipartisan cooperation in an increasingly divided Congress.",
              "lineHeight": 1.7,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "y78c1",
              "name": "h2a",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "content": "A Historic Transportation Investment ",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 20,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "line",
              "id": "4xNLp",
              "name": "Divider",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 0,
              "stroke": {
                "thickness": 1,
                "fill": "$--border"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "yGCLU",
              "name": "body2",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "At the heart of the proposal lies an unprecedented $890 billion allocation for transportation infrastructure. The plan would fund the repair or replacement of more than 45,000 structurally deficient bridges, resurface hundreds of thousands of miles of highways, and expand public transit systems in both urban and rural communities across the country.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "JudWj",
              "name": "Body Paragraph 1",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The proposal, which has been months in the making, represents a significant shift in Washington's approach to infrastructure spending. Unlike previous attempts that stalled along party lines, this package was crafted through extensive negotiations between senior members of both parties, with input from governors, mayors, and industry leaders across the country.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "c2f53",
              "name": "H2 Transportation",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "A Historic Investment in Transportation",
              "lineHeight": 1.3,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 20,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "1wEPp",
              "name": "Body Paragraph 2",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "At the heart of the plan is a massive investment in the nation's transportation infrastructure. With an estimated 45,000 bridges classified as structurally deficient and countless miles of highway in desperate need of repair, the transportation crisis has been building for decades. The bill allocates $621 billion specifically for roads, bridges, and major transit projects.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "cSTyk",
              "name": "H2 Broadband",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Broadband for All Americans",
              "lineHeight": 1.3,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 20,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "caOfL",
              "name": "Body Paragraph 3",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Perhaps the most transformative element of the package is its commitment to universal broadband access. The plan dedicates $100 billion to ensuring that every American household has access to affordable, high-speed internet by 2030. This provision has drawn particular support from rural legislators, who have long argued that the digital divide is holding back economic development in their communities.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "J1SPa",
              "name": "h2b",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "content": "Broadband for All Americans",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 20,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "3A08h",
              "name": "body3",
              "fill": "$--foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Perhaps the most forward-looking element of the proposal is its $420 billion investment in universal broadband access. The plan aims to bring high-speed internet to every American household by 2030, with particular emphasis on rural and underserved communities that have been left behind in the digital revolution.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "OKgrG",
              "name": "Article Image",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 220,
              "fill": {
                "type": "image",
                "enabled": true,
                "url": "./images/generated-1774470987298.png",
                "mode": "fill"
              },
              "cornerRadius": 8
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
